   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LIPIZZANER-HORSES (Lipica, Slovenia) _ If one-trick ponies
dream, they dream of being Lipizzaners. But in the age of
globalization, even dreams of white horses need their fine print
reviewed by a lawyer. Both the European Union and the World Trade
Organization have been drawn into a dispute over what exactly makes
a horse an official descendant of those first bred in this mountain
hamlet in 1580. By Donald G. McNeil Jr.
