<P>
   EUROPE-INTERNET (London) _ Not too long ago, Web-users across
Europe were hostage to former state monopolies like France Telecom,
Deutsche Telekom and British Telecommunications. Now, as a host of
start-up service providers, cable companies and American
interlopers jostle to ride the coming wave of Europe-online, these
find they must compete or lose business on the local phone charges
that once provided their most profitable mainstay. ``This is the
land-grab that's going on for the European Internet,'' said Peter
Bradshaw, an analyst with Merrill Lynch. ``And clearly everyone is
seeking to get the most consumers on their own portal. This is a
war that will be decided very quickly.'' By Alan Cowell.
