and interest depend on the outcome of the Super Tuesday votes.
(Crowley, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   YOUNGVOTERS _ For the first time, the entire population known as
Generation X _ whose members range in age from 18 to about 35 _ is
eligible to vote. In November they will represent about 40 percent
of all eligible voters. Both parties are making efforts to attract
and turn out the youth vote, and the primaries offer some insight
on how successful those efforts may be in the fall. (Montgomery,
Dayton Daily News). Second in The Voters series w/The Voters sig.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This story was offered prviously but has been updated and
is being offered again.
</P>
<P>
   STRATEGY _ This story looks at how effective the campaign staffs
are for Vice President Al Gore and Texas Gov. George W. Bush. The
consensus is that Gore's staff shake-up and re-location early on
served him well, but that Bush is in a weaker position because of
the amount of money he had to spend and his tactic of changing
messages as well as himself as he appealed to different electorates
and different political bosses. (Heath, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
