<SLUG> BC-NY-PATROL-SHOT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KILLING STUNS HOUSING PROJECT IN FAR ROCKAWAY 
</HEADLINE>
   (jw) 
 By TINA KELLEY   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Residents of a Far Rockaway housing project are reeling from the
shooting death Friday night of one of their tenant patrol
volunteers, who was killed by a stray bullet when two groups opened
fire.
</P>
<P>
   Maria Medina, 45, a resident of the Redfern Houses, had been
helping a friend on duty at the front desk when she was shot.
</P>
<P>
   Margaret Contreras, 46, said that although Medina had strep
throat and had not been scheduled for front desk duty, she
volunteered to sit with Contreras, who was alone at the front desk,
until she was to be relieved, around 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   When the shots broke out soon after, Contreras started crawling
toward the elevator. ``She turned to me and said, `Margie, Margie,
I'm shot, I'm shot,''' Contreras said. ``We picked her up by the
legs, and put her on the elevator.''
</P>
<P>
   Medina's younger daughter, Stacey, 11, rode in the elevator with
them to the fourth floor, where Contreras lives. Stacey's
godmother, Shirleen Green, 40, was also on the elevator.
</P>
<P>
   ``I held her in the elevator,'' Green said. ``I can't get that
image out of my mind. I kept telling her `Hold on, baby.'''
</P>
<P>
   Police officers were posted in the stairwells at every floor of
the six-story building on Saturday. At first, police thought the
shooter was still in the building, but said Saturday that they no
longer thought so.
</P>
<P>
   ``Apparently several shots were exchanged between two groups
outside,'' said Sgt. Rafael Andalia. ``Some of the shots, stray
rounds, entered the lobby.'' Ten to 15 shots were fired, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Another member of the tenant patrol reported seeing four men
running away, but no one had been arrested by Saturday afternoon,
and the police were still looking for suspects.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not ruling anything out,'' Andalia said.
</P>
<P>
   Medina, who had three children, started working on the tenant
patrol about two months ago, two or three times a week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
