and interest depend on the outcome of the Super Tuesday votes.
(Crowley, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   STRATEGY _ This story looks at how effective the campaign staffs
are for Vice President Al Gore and Texas Gov. George W. Bush. The
consensus is that Gore's staff shake-up and re-location early on
served him well, but that Bush is in a weaker position because of
the amount of money he had to spend and his tactic of changing
messages as well as himself as he appealed to different electorates
and different political bosses. (Heath, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
