<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Saturday, 03/11/00. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) NEW YORK -- March 11, 2000 -- BKN-NOTEBOOK -- Sean
Elliott has a decent chance of stepping onto the court of the
Alamodome in San Antonio on Tuesday night, marking his first
appearance this season. Becoming the first professional athlete
known to resume his career after a kidney transplant, the Spurs'
32-year-old swingman will most likely receive a prolonged,
emotional ovation. Elliott had his blood pressure checked Saturday
by Joe Gutzwiller, the Spurs' assistant trainer. (Vincent
LaForet/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) GRAFTON, N.Y. -- March 11, 2000 -- NY-BIRDMAN-2 -- Peter
J. Dubacher runs a sanctuary at his parents' farm in Grafton for
birds that have been injured or are no longer wanted. ``I'm not a
religious person, but I do believe, as humans, we all have a
responsibility'' said Dubacher, 51, who makes room for them all
because he cannot bear the thought of what would happen otherwise.
A sandhill crane watched over chickens, guinea fowl and pigeons in
one of the barns here. (David Jennings/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) GRAFTON, N.Y. -- March 11, 2000 -- NY-BIRDMAN-1 -- In
the last quarter century, Peter J. Dubacher, shown handling an
American bald eagle, has run a sanctuary at his parents' farm in
Grafton for birds that have been injured or are no longer wanted.
By his count, Dubacher, 51, cares for 1,700 birds - including 15
eagles, 2 peregrine falcons, and 19 emus - in a maze of greenhouses
and wooden pens. (David Jennings/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) NEW YORK -- March 11, 2000 -- BKC-RHODEN-COLUMN -- Erick
Barkley, who scored 7 points in St. John's victory in the Big East
semifinals Friday, made a stunning announcement afterward. After
the exhilarating 1-point victory, Barkley, dejected and near tears,
told reporters he was taking a leave of absence. (Chang W. Lee/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) TAMPA, Fla. -- March 11, 2000 -- BBA-YANKS-JETER --
Derek Jeter, the Yankees 25-year-old shortstop, is such a good
hitter that even when fooled, he is capable of hitting a pitch just
above his shoes or off the outside corner and dumping a single into
right field. But he is also apt to swing at a bad pitch and ground
out to second base. If Jeter amassed another 15 seasons at his
current rate of success, he would approach 4,000 hits and 2,000
runs scored. But there is room for improvement. (Barton
Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- March 11, 2000 -- NY-WOODY-CRUSADE-2 --
Woody Allen has made a short film for the Landmarks Preservation
