   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   PUBLIC-RADIO-HOST _ I was intrigued this week by a profile in
``The New York Times'' on Terry Gross, a name well-known to
listeners of public radio. She's the host of an arts program called
``Fresh Air'', on which she affably interviews a vast array of
authors, musicians, actors, directors and the like, picking their
brains on why and how they think the things they think and create
the things they do. (Rollins, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SXSW-ADVANCE _ AUSTIN _ Short primer on what SXSW is, what it
really is, what's in store for this year, how much it costs, what
you can see for free, etc. (Riemenschneider, Austin
American-Statesman). 15. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SXSW-MONEY _ On the Sunday before the SXSW music conference
begins, this front page story examines the shift in sponsorship at
the music festival. Not surprisingly, web company money is all the
rage, with record companies taking a back seat to this new money.
We look at why this shift occurred and how it will affect the
festival and conference. (Riemenschneider, Austin
American-Statesman). 44. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   VANGOGH _ Advance and preview of the big new Van Gogh exhibition
at the Detroit Institute of Art. Brings together 70 of his painted
and drawn portraits. (Black, Dayton Daily News). 35. MOVED
