   6.(x) HARRY POTTER AND THE SORCERER'S STONE,
</P>
<P>
   by J.K. Rowling. (Scholastic, $5.99.) A British
</P>
<P>
   boy, neglected by his relatives, finds his fortune
</P>
<P>
   attending a school for witchcraft.
</P>
<P>
   7. A SEASON BEYOND A KISS, by Kathleen E. Woodiwiss.
</P>
<P>
   (Avon, $14.) In the early 19th century, a woman's marriage
</P>
<P>
   to a shipping magnate is endangered by the cruel rumors
</P>
<P>
   that bedevil him.
</P>
<P>
   8. SEND NO FLOWERS, by Sandra Brown. (Bantam, $6.99.)
</P>
<P>
   A young widowed mother embarks on an affair with an
</P>
<P>
   enigmatic man.
</P>
<P>
   9.(x) CERTAIN PREY, by John Sandford. (Berkley, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   Lucas Davenport pursues a woman who is a longtime
</P>
<P>
   successful hired killer.
</P>
<P>
   10. A MAP OF THE WORLD, by Jane Hamilton. (Anchor,
</P>
<P>
   $12.95.) When a dairy farmer's wife makes a mistake
</P>
<P>
   one morning, her life falls apart.
</P>
<P>
   11. THE CIDER HOUSE RULES, by John Irving. (Ballantine,
</P>
<P>
   $7.99.) Life in a Maine orphanage in the first part of
</P>
<P>
   the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
   12. MISTAKEN IDENTITY, by Lisa Scottoline. ......
</P>
<P>
   (HarperPaperbacks, $7.50.) Will a lawyer's client,
</P>
<P>
   accused of murder, turn out to be her twin?
</P>
<P>
   13. FIRST LADY, by Susan Elizabeth Phillips. (Avon, $6.99.)
</P>
<P>
   A young widow who was married to the president of the
</P>
<P>
   United States finds a new love.
</P>
<P>
   14. THE GREEN MILE, by Stephen King. (Pocket, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   A six-part thriller set on death row at Cold Mountain
</P>
<P>
   Penitentiary.
</P>
<P>
   15. THE HOURS, by Michael Cunningham. (Picador, USA, $13.)
</P>
